{
  "name": "Shark Tooth",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Hoshigaki.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Clan Prerequisite: Hoshigaki Clan, Level 8+ </p><p>Your Body has begun to adapt to deep sea exploration and the hunt. <br />Your teeth grow sharper and more serrated. <br />You gain the following Benefits:</p><p> </p><p>• Increase your Strength or Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20. </p><p><br />• You gain proficiency in Strength saving throws while you are submerged in water. </p><p><br />• You gain access to a Bite Attack. <br />You can replace one or more of your attacks made with the attack action, with this bite attack. <br />Your bite attack has the following statistics and abilities:</p><p>   • Deals 3d4 + Strength piercing damage. </p><p><br />   • Creatures who take damage from your bite, must make a Strength saving throw vs your Taijutsu save DC, being grappled on a failed save. <br />You can only grapple one creature at a time this way. </p><p><br />   • When you deal 12 or more damage with a single bite attack, the target gains one rank of bleeding.</p>",
